source_quote: The first FVG inside the session is important. It will often act as a breakaway gap or an inverse gap

signature.condition: IF the first FVG forms inside the session
signature.action: THEN treat it as important - it will often act as a breakaway gap or an inverse gap that will be traded to later
signature.drawer_basis: describes FVG behavior pattern for entry/target identification

source_quote: Market maker small 5/15 min models start when the Daily direction order flow gets exhausted. When exhausted go to 4hr time frame

signature.condition: IF Daily direction order flow gets exhausted
signature.action: THEN market maker small 5/15 min models start - go to 4hr time frame for levels
signature.drawer_basis: describes HTF exhaustion triggering LTF model activation

source_quote: Which 15min FVG to use? Look at 1hr OB

signature.condition: IF uncertain which 15min FVG to use
signature.action: THEN look at 1hr OB for guidance
signature.drawer_basis: HTF OB provides confirmation for LTF FVG selection

source_quote: In the last stages of MMM pull back will be quick and to the nearest order block

signature.condition: IF price is in the last stages of MMM (market maker model)
signature.action: THEN pull back will be quick and to the nearest order block
signature.drawer_basis: describes market structure behavior in late-stage MMM

source_quote: @ICT When price is likely NOT to return to OB? = If we have a BPR above/below it

signature.condition: IF there is a BPR (balanced price range) above or below an order block
signature.action: THEN price is likely NOT to return to that OB
signature.drawer_basis: BPR position relative to OB determines retracement probability

source_quote: When price enters external liquidity on the higher TF and hits our targets, our focus goes to the lower TF opposite liquidity levels

signature.condition: IF price enters external liquidity on the higher TF and hits our targets
signature.action: THEN focus goes to the lower TF opposite liquidity levels (20day range, most focus on last 5day range)
signature.drawer_basis: HTF target achievement shifts focus to LTF opposing liquidity

source_quote: Which FVG is highest probability? - the one that forms inside of the kill zone at specific time

signature.condition: IF FVG forms inside of the kill zone at specific time
signature.action: THEN that FVG is highest probability
signature.drawer_basis: killzone timing explicitly determines FVG quality for entry

source_quote: 4hr - is FVG strong? Did it form during key times? Did 1hr already filled this FVG?

signature.action: THEN check if it formed during key times and if 1hr already filled this FVG
signature.drawer_basis: time of formation and LTF fill status confirm FVG validity

source_quote: WHEN PRICE SITS ON A WEEKLY OPENING, DOES NOT TAKE LIQUIDITY BUT STARTS SHARPLY MOVE AWAY FROM IT WITH NICE LOWS/HIGHS AND FVG'S - ENTER

signature.condition: IF price sits on a weekly opening AND does not take liquidity AND starts sharply moving away from it with nice lows/highs and FVGs
signature.drawer_basis: explicit entry trigger based on weekly open behavior

source_quote: Option A: Strong protraction, running liquidity (ideally into opposing PDA's and during one of the KZ's) leaving sharp/strong structure

signature.condition: IF strong protraction occurs AND runs liquidity (ideally into opposing PDAs during killzone) AND leaves sharp/strong structure AND ETFs shift into clear order flow
signature.action: THEN this is Option A entry setup
signature.drawer_basis: explicitly labeled as entry option with specific conditions

source_quote: Option B: Price giving a strong isolation, strong 31st L type of structure from where it is IF we can't trust the current price action

signature.condition: IF price gives strong isolation AND strong 31st L type of structure AND current price action cannot be trusted AND occurs during killzone
signature.action: THEN this is Option B entry setup
signature.drawer_basis: explicitly labeled as entry option for untrusted PA conditions

source_quote: Option C: Looking for order flow to continue on the LTF's to the point where it wouldn't make sense for LTF's to drop

signature.condition: IF order flow continues on LTF to the point where it wouldn't make sense for LTFs to drop all the way running liquidity that's already far away
signature.action: THEN this is Option C entry setup - look for continuation
signature.drawer_basis: explicitly labeled as entry option based on LTF order flow continuation
